# LMFDB level-1 modular form orbit `1.182.a.{a..}` (Hecke field degree 14)

The Hecke field `K = ℚ(α)` is degree 14 over ℚ. The LMFDB lists q-coefficients as
elements of `K`, which we decompose as `c_0 + c_1 · α + … + c_{13} · α^13`.
The combined form is `f = f_0 + α · f_1 + … + α^13 · f_{13}`, with each
`f_j` a level-1 weight-182 form with rational coefficients in `(E₄, E₆)`.

